      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"9. HESAA LISTER has been racing at Menangle where he has been very consistent, recording a win and four placings from the last five starts. Drew very wide last week but had enough speed to find the front before boxing on for a 4m third. His form is good enough to win this if things go his way from the back row. 1. TIGER EUPHEME retired from the event after sulky contact last start but was going very well prior with a string of placings at this venue. Should get every chance from the ace draw. 8. BEV THE GOAT is a newcomer to the Troy Williams yard from Queensland where her form was sound, finishing third from this row at Redcliffe when last seen six weeks ago. 7. CARIBBEAN RUNA draws for a trail and can be competitive.\",\"runners\":[9,1,8,7],\"exclusive\":false}",
